<p>You can use the text box below to search for the definition of a word (you should search for the word without case markers, and plain form verbs). The results will be displayed below.</p>
<p id="dictLookupReturnZone"></p>
<input type="text" id="dictLookup" oninput="lookupWord = this.value">
<button onclick="dictLookup(lookupWord, lookupType)">lookup</button>
<button onclick="clearDictLookup()">clear</button>
<p>Search by...</p>
<select name="dictLookupSearchType" id="dictLookupSearchType" oninput="lookupType = this.value" value="word">
<option value="word">Word</option>
<option value="root">Root</option>
<option value="rootLength">Root length</option>
<option value="noun">Nouns</option>
<option value="adj">Adjectives</option>
<option value="verb">Verbs</option>
</select>
<p><b>We've finished porting to JavaScript! ðŸŽ‰</b><br>
<b>Known issues:</b><br>
  - When the imperative is used, the subject of the sentence does not use the vocative (despite that the imperative is used to address someone directly and shouldn't take a subject.)<br>
  - The question marker <i>ma</i> can be used on sentences that realistically cannot be a question, like the plain and imperative.<br>
  <strike>- Sometimes the generator can use more tenses than explicitly permitted. I don't know why this happens.</strike> Should be fixed!<br>
  - In some circumstances, instead of a verb being written in the sentence, "TEMP" will be written instead (and tenses suffixed onto it).<br>
  - In certain cases where the minimum tenses is very high, the amount of tenses used may be less than the minimum tenses required. This is because of some behind the scenes stuff to do with ensuring the plain and imperative tenses don't take illegal tenses: even though it does generate the minimum number of tenses, some of those tenses are removed when it decides to use the plain / imperative. This is essentially unfixable.<br>
  - Presumably myriad other bugs and issues I haven't encountered through testing yet.<br>
  As per usual, if you see any bugs, please report them on the Adamantine's Drainbox thread of the <a href="https://yongasabi.freeforums.net/">Yongasabi Forums</a>.
</p>
